  "prompt": "Is Kyiv (Kiev) radioactive?",
  "response": "No, Kyiv (formerly known as Kiev) is not radioactive. The city of Kyiv, the capital of Ukraine, is not affected by significant radioactive contamination. The Chernobyl disaster, which occurred in 1986, did result in radioactive contamination in areas surrounding the Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant, particularly the nearby town of Pripyat. However, Kyiv is located approximately 100 kilometers (about 62 miles) south of Chernobyl and was not directly impacted by the radiation from the disaster to the extent of making the city itself radioactive. Routine monitoring and safety measures have been in place since the disaster to ensure that areas outside the exclusion zone, including Kyiv, remain safe for residents and visitors.",
